& [SourceSet] is the checked research surface
  + [source_001] is Atserias, Bulatov, and Dalmau, On the power of k-consistency
    = url: https://www.cs.upc.edu/~atserias/papers/abd07-k-width/abd07-k-width.pdf
    = relevance: connects k-consistency, bounded width, and resolution-style limitations for CSPs
  + [source_002] is Barto and Kozik, Constraint Satisfaction Problems of Bounded Width
    = url: https://www.karlin.mff.cuni.cz/~barto/Articles/SDBW.pdf
    = relevance: characterizes when local consistency checking solves nonuniform CSPs
  + [source_003] is Dalmau, Kolaitis, and Vardi, Constraint Satisfaction, Bounded Treewidth, and Finite-Variable Logics
    = url: https://www.cs.rice.edu/~vardi/papers/cp02.pdf
    = relevance: links bounded treewidth, finite-variable logic, and CSP tractability/definability
  + [source_004] is Mitchell, Resolution and Constraint Satisfaction
    = url: https://cse.unl.edu/~choueiry/Documents/DMitchell-cp03-res.pdf
    = relevance: studies resolution-like refutation systems for CSP and common CSP algorithms
  + [source_005] is Vardi et al., Constraint Propagation as a Proof System
    = url: https://www.cs.rice.edu/~vardi/papers/cp041.pdf
    = relevance: compares constraint-propagation proof systems to resolution, Gaussian calculus, cutting planes, and bounded-depth Frege
  + [source_006] is Nordstrom, Proof Complexity and SAT Solving
    = url: https://jakobnordstrom.se/docs/publications/ProofComplexityChapter.pdf
    = relevance: explains SAT solvers as proof systems and reviews proof-complexity limits for resolution and stronger systems
  + [source_007] is Raghavendra et al., Sum of squares lower bounds for refuting any CSP
    = url: https://www.cs.cmu.edu/~odonnell/papers/csp-sos-lower-bounds.pdf
    = relevance: shows lower bounds for strong refutation algorithms in random CSP settings

& [ResearchResolution] is the proof-complexity result
  + [confirmed_001_local_consistency_has_known_complete_scope] is local consistency can solve bounded-width or bounded-structure CSP classes
  + [confirmed_002_np_complete_scope_is_exactly_the_escape] is NP-complete CSP/SAT scope is not captured by bounded local consistency unless P equals NP by a separate breakthrough
  + [confirmed_003_unsat_certificates_are_proof_system_objects] is propagation fixed-point refutations correspond to proof systems with known strength and limitations
  + [confirmed_004_polynomial_certificates_are_not_general] is no checked source provides polynomial-size local-propagation unsat certificates for all SAT/3-SAT hard fixed points
  + [confirmed_005_lower_bounds_support_caution] is proof complexity contains lower-bound phenomena showing that many refutation systems require large proofs on hard instances

